Indian Uranium Mine May Be World’s Biggest, Business Line Says

-- B y   R a j e s h   K u m a r   S i n g h
-- 
2011-07-19T03:17:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/indian-uranium-mine-may-be-world-s-biggest-business-line-says.html
India ’s southern state of Andhra
Pradesh may hold the largest uranium reserves in the world, the
Business Line newspaper reported, citing the Department of
Atomic Energy.  A survey is being conducted at the Tummalappalle mine in
Cuddapah district and the reserves may be triple the current
estimate of 49,000 metric tons of ore, the report cited Srikumar Banerjee, secretary at the Department of Atomic Energy, as
saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rajesh Kumar Singh in  New Delhi  at 
